    "29941187": {
      "title": "Arrow's theorem: unusual domains and extended codomains",
      "abstract": "Abstract In this paper we establish Arrow's theorem in a general ordinal case. When some configurations are allowed in the domain and if this domain is included in the codomain, the only social functions satisfying the independence condition and the weak Pareto Principle are the absolute dictatorships or the absolute oligarchies."
